In ancient Hawaii, Kukini were an elite class of men selected to undergo strenuous physical and mental training to become swift foot runners. Such runners were used in battles, as messengers, spies, and as athletes in foot racing.

[[Hawaiian language]] for "swift and valued runner."

The shoe corporation, Nike, used the name Kukini for one of the models of their running shoes apparently based on this history.

